{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/settingsschemaprotocol"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SettingsSchemaProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Plugin loading systems that wish to provide plugins a way to access","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"settings face the problem of how to make the schemas for these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"settings visible to GSettings.  Typically, a plugin will want to ship"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the schema along with itself and it won’t be installed into the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"standard system directories for schemas.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaSource","type":"reference"},{"text":"] provides a mechanism for dealing with this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"by allowing the creation of a new ‘schema source’ from which schemas can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be acquired.  This schema source can then become part of the metadata","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"associated with the plugin and queried whenever the plugin requires"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"access to some settings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["typedef struct","{","   …","   GSettingsSchemaSource *schema_source;","   …","} Plugin;","","Plugin *","initialise_plugin (const gchar *dir)","{","  Plugin *plugin;","","  …","","  plugin->schema_source =","    g_settings_schema_source_new_from_directory (dir,","      g_settings_schema_source_get_default (), FALSE, NULL);","","  …","","  return plugin;","}","","…","","GSettings *","plugin_get_settings (Plugin      *plugin,","                     const gchar *schema_id)","{","  GSettingsSchema *schema;","","  if (schema_id == NULL)","    schema_id = plugin->identifier;","","  schema = g_settings_schema_source_lookup (plugin->schema_source,","                                            schema_id, FALSE);","","  if (schema == NULL)","    {","      … disable the plugin or abort, etc …","    }","","  return g_settings_new_full (schema, NULL, NULL);","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The code above shows how hooks should be added to the code that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialises (or enables) the plugin to create the schema source and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how an API can be added to the plugin system to provide a convenient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"way for the plugin to access its settings, using the schemas that it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ships."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"From the standpoint of the plugin, it would need to ensure that it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ships a gschemas.compiled file as part of itself, and then simply do"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["{","  GSettings *settings;","  gint some_value;","","  settings = plugin_get_settings (self, NULL);","  some_value = g_settings_get_int (settings, \"some-value\");","  …","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s also possible that the plugin system expects the schema source"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"files (ie: "},{"code":".gschema.xml","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" files) instead of a "},{"code":"gschemas.compiled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case, the plugin loading system must compile the schemas for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"itself before attempting to create the settings source.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSettingsSchema"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchema"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/id","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/path","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/settings_schema_ptr-9ce3j"],"generated":true},{"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/getID()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/getKey(name:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/getPath()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/hasKey(name:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/listChildren()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/listKeys()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/ref()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaProtocol\/unref()"],"generated":true}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO22SettingsSchemaProtocolP","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SettingsSchemaProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"SettingsSchemaProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SettingsSchemaProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchemaSource"},{"text":"] and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSettingsSchema"},{"text":" APIs provide a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"mechanism for advanced control over the loading of schemas and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"mechanism for introspecting their content.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SettingsSchema","doc:\/\/GIO\